    <h1 property="name" id="wb-cont" dir="ltr">
EI Sickness Benefits: What these benefits offer</h1>
        <div><div class="mwsgeneric-base-html parbase section">
<div>
  <div class="mrgn-tp-md mrgn-bttm-lg brdr-bttm">
    <div class="row">
      <ul class="toc lst-spcd col-md-12">
        <li class="col-md-4"> <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/services/benefits/ei/ei-sickness.html" class="list-group-item active">1. What these benefits offer</a> </li>
        <li class="col-md-4"> <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/services/benefits/ei/ei-sickness/eligibility.html" class="list-group-item">2. Eligibility</a> </li>
        <li class="col-md-4"> <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/services/benefits/ei/ei-sickness/benefit-amount.html" class="list-group-item">3. How much you could receive</a> </li>
        <li class="col-md-4"> <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/services/benefits/ei/ei-sickness/before-applying.html" class="list-group-item">4. Apply</a> </li>
        <li class="col-md-4"> <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/services/benefits/ei/ei-sickness/apply.html" class="list-group-item">5. After you apply</a> </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-8">
		<section>
      <p>Employment Insurance (EI) sickness benefits can provide you  with up to 15 weeks of financial assistance if you cannot work for medical  reasons. You could receive 55% of your earnings up to a maximum of $562 a week.</p>
      <p>You must get a medical certificate to show that you&rsquo;re  unable to work for medical reasons. Medical reasons include illness, injury,  quarantine or any medical condition that prevents you from working.</p>
		<details>
		<summary><strong>Find out if you have employer-paid sick leave<</strong>/summary>
			<p>Some employers provide their own paid sick leave plan. Before you apply for EI sickness benefits, check with your employer to find out if they have a program in place.</p>
		</details>
			<details>
				<summary>If you have a long-term or permanent disability</summary>			
				<p>If your  medical condition is expected to be long-term or permanent, you may be eligible  for other benefits such as:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/services/benefits/publicpensions/cpp/cpp-disability-benefit.html">Canada Pension Plan  Disability benefits</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.rrq.gouv.qc.ca/en/programmes/regime_rentes/prestations_invalidite/Pages/prestations_invalidite.aspx">Quebec Pension Plan  Disability benefits</a></li>
            </ul>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>If you get sick or require bedrest during pregnancy</summary>
			<p>If you have health complications during pregnancy, you  could be eligible for sickness  benefits or for <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/services/benefits/ei/ei-maternity-parental.html">maternity benefits</a>. You must meet the conditions for each benefit.<strong> </strong></p>
			</details>
</section>
<nav role="navigation">
  <h2 class="wb-inv">Document navigation</h2>
